The paper deals with channel tracking and parameter estimation in wireless relay networks, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm involves Bayesian state space modeling and Monte Carlo methods, which are also relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of particle Markov chain Monte Carlo (PMCMC) method and Sequential Monte Carlo (SMC) filter suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.AI) and probabilistic modeling (cs.LG).
